{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3551301,"name":"mbhoxsie","username":"mbhoxsie","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mbhoxsie/{size}/10287_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-08T18:43:30.927Z","cooked":"<p>My team is currently using the <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> generated swerve drive and we are trying to build command to auto align on the reef and human player station april tags.</p>
<p>We have the limelight configured and ready and thought we had the swerve drive request for robot centric driving figured out, but each time we go to execute the command, we don’t get movement.</p>
<p>We removed the limelight logic to just apply the Swerve  request on a button press, and still no movement and so we know we are probably not calling the swerve request correctly.</p>
<p>Here is the syntax of initalizing the swerve drive request:<br>
<em>drive = SwerveRequest.RobotCentric().withDriveRequestType(DriveRequestType.Velocity)</em>;</p>
<p>When we go to apply the request, we pass it this way (with Vx = -1.0 and Vy = -1.0 and Omega = 45 degrees (converted to radians)):<br>
// Drive the robot (robot-relative)*<br>
m_drivetrain.applyRequest(() → drive*<br>
.withVelocityX(m_Vy) // Drive*<br>
// forward*<br>
// with*<br>
// negative*<br>
// Y*<br>
// (forward)*<br>
.withVelocityY(m_Vx) // Drive*<br>
// left*<br>
// with*<br>
// negative X (left)*<br>
.withRotationalRate(m_Omega));*</p>
<p>Any thoughts on anything we are missing?   Any switches options or configuration settings?</p>
<p>Thanks!! <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slight_smile.png?v=12" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2025-03-08T18:44:37.901Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":41,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":215.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494755,"topic_slug":"robot-centric-swerve-requests","display_username":"mbhoxsie","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":34100,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/robot-centric-swerve-requests/494755/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3551347,"name":"Miles","username":"mhelve46","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/b3f665/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-08T19:48:33.269Z","cooked":"<p>Try replacing applyRequest() with setControl(). I don’t know why it is different, but this is what we did in our code and it works.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2025-03-08T19:48:33.269Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":47,"readers_count":46,"score":39.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":494755,"topic_slug":"robot-centric-swerve-requests","display_username":"Miles","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"fla